git init // to initialise the git
git status // to track the status
git add index.html the file will go from modification to staging
to unstage it we can use git rm --cached index.html

going to staging to commit zone
git commit  -m " write message like initial message"
git log // it show commkit snapshots
git log --oneline// it more readable format
git  --global user// sets global identity
git add . // to add in single go use this command
git config --global user.name "mahrishi_rathore"
git config user.name  // it give the name
git conf -- global user.email "mahrishisinghrathore@gmail.com"
clear // terminal clearing comand

there are three zones
modification--------------------- staging------------------ commit

untracked zone                      check point
index.html                             whether to commit           gti commit
 git add index.html                       or not
